<table width="600">
	<tr>
		<td>
			<h1 align="center">ImageRover</h1>
			<hr>			
		
			<p><b>Developed by:</b><br> Boston University, MA</p>
			
			<p>
			<b>Features:</b><br> 
			- Extracts color and texture orientation features.<br>
			- System computes over 6 subregions (whole, central, and 4 corners) to form 2 x 6 sub-vectors
			</p>
			
			<p>
			<b>Matching:</b><br>
			- Normalized Minkowski metric is used to compute distance between two sets of vectors.
			</p>
			
			<p>
			<b>Querying:</b><br>
			1) User starts with sets of keyword.<br>
			2) Then, after the system returns results back, user can mark images for relevance.
			</p>
			
			<p align="center">
			<i>Fig 1. Result window of ImageRover.</i><br>
			<i>
			<img border="0" src="images/imagerover/imagerover.jpg" width="692" height="626"><br>
			&nbsp;</i></p>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
